 directly from the transcript using `extractCheckpointPrompts()` (line 472)\\n\\n**Process:**\\n```\\nextractSessionData()\\n  → reads transcript from shadow branch tree\\n  → calls extractCheckpointPrompts(agentType, transcript, checkpointTranscriptStart)\\n    → extracts user prompts directly from JSONL/JSON transcript\\n  → returns ExtractedSessionData with extracted prompts\\n```\\n\\n**Location: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go::extractCheckpointPrompts()` (lines 575-607)**\\n\\nThis function:\\n- Takes the full transcript\\n- Scopes it to the checkpoint portion using `checkpointTranscriptStart`\\n- Calls `extractUserPrompts()` to parse user messages from the transcript\\n- **Completely bypasses `prompt.txt`**\\n\\n### 4. **How prompt.txt is Written to the Committed Metadata Branch**\\n\\n**Location: `cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go::writeSessionToSubdirectory()` (lines 351-364)**\\n\\n- Takes `opts.Prompts` (which came from `extractCheckpointPrompts()`)\\n- Joins them with `\\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\"` separator\\n- Creates a blob and stores it at `sessionPath + paths.PromptFileName`\\n- This is written to the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n\\n**Structure on committed branch:**\\n```\\nentire/checkpoints/v1:/a3/b2c4d5e6f7/\\n  ├── metadata.json (CheckpointSummary)\\n  └── 0/ (first session)\\n      ├── metadata.json (CommittedMetadata)\\n      ├── full.jsonl\\n      ├── prompt.txt (written from extracted prompts)\\n      └── content_hash.txt\\n```\\n\\n### 5. **Key Insight: The Data Flow**\\n\\n```\\nShadow Branch Checkpoint:\\n  .entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt\\n              ↓\\n         (NOT read during condensation!)\\n              ↓\\n       extractSessionData() reads transcript instead\\n              ↓\\n    extractCheckpointPrompts() parses prompts from transcript\\n              ↓\\n          opts.Prompts = [...] (extracted from transcript)\\n              ↓\\n    Committed Branch Checkpoint:\\n         <ch