on\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T00:40:26.827Z\"},\"cmd/entire/cli/status.go\":{\"backupFileName\":\"28eb2b40f38b633c@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T00:40:26.827Z\"},\"cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go\":{\"backupFileName\":\"bc109ec266755ce0@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T00:40:26.827Z\"},\"cmd/entire/cli/status_test.go\":{\"backupFileName\":\"ad42f4dbdb3bd07a@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T00:40:26.827Z\"},\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/.claude/plans/serene-churning-pudding.md\":{\"backupFileName\":\"006bf3fb74cc7893@v1\",\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-03T00:49:59.712Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T00:40:26.826Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c9ac8d5a-4aac-46b9-894c-cc6a5db71847\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0d411808-78e1-4abb-b5da-ab760ebccc55\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"571-remove-contextmd-and-simplify-prompttxt-to-checkpoint-prompts-only\",\"slug\":\"serene-churning-pudding\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_018Kg3hxAiRQL18kMrRatAZk\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01JJgGfNFrA6mAATwrY1VNyY\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/.claude/plans/serene-churning-pudding.md\",\"content\":\"# Plan: Fix prompt.txt missing in mid-turn commit checkpoints\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nMid-turn commits (agent commits while still working) produce checkpoints without `prompt.txt` after the first one. The root cause: after the first condensation advances `CheckpointTranscriptStart`, `extractCheckpointPrompts()` scopes the transcript past where the prompt lives.\\n\\nThe previous approach (repurposing `FirstPrompt` → `LastPrompt` on session state) was rejected as too invasive and not aligned with the architecture. The user wants the shadow branch to be the source of truth, not the transcript.\\n\\n## Root Cause Detail\\n\\n1. Agent commits mid-turn → PostCommit → `CondenseSession` → `extractSessionData`\\n2. First checkpoint: `extractCheckpointPrompts(transcript, offset=0)` finds the prompt ✓\\n3. After condensation: `CheckpointTranscriptStart` advances to end of transcript\\n4. If all files were committed (no carry-forward), `CheckpointTranscriptStart` stays advanced\\n5. Agent commits again → `extractCheckpointPrompts(transcript, offset=advanced)` scopes past prompt ✗\\n\\nNote: carry-forward resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0`, so this bug only manifests when all files are committed (no carry-forward).\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n**Write `prompt.txt` to the filesystem at turn start, then read it from the shadow branch or filesystem during condensation — not from the transcript.**\\n\\n### Why this works\\n- At turn start, we have the user prompt (`event.Prompt`) — write it to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt`\\n- During mid-turn condensation, read `prompt.txt` from: shadow branch tree → filesystem → transcript (fallback)\\n- At turn end, `CreateSessionCheckpoint` overwrites `prompt.txt` with the properly extracted version, then `SaveStep` commits it to the shadow branch\\n- The shadow branch remains the source of truth after SaveStep\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Write `prompt.txt` at turn start\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`** — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~line 113):\\n\\nAfter `CapturePrePromptState` and before `InitializeSession`, write the user prompt to `prompt.txt`:\\n\\n```go\\n// Write prompt.txt early so it's available for mid-turn commits.\\n// CreateSessionCheckpoint will overwrite this with the full extracted version at turn end.\\nif event.Prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)\\n    if sessionDirAbs, absErr := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir); absErr == nil {\\n        if mkErr := os.MkdirAll(sessionDirAbs, 0o750); mkErr == nil {\\n            promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n            _ = os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(event.Prompt), 0o600)\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis is best-effort (errors silently ignored) — the transcript fallback still exists.\\n\\n### 2. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch in `extractSessionData`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionData()` (~line 464):\\n\\nReplace transcript-based prompt extraction with shadow branch tree read + filesystem fallback:\\n\\n```go\\n// Read prompts from shadow branch tree (source of truth after SaveStep)\\nif file, fileErr := tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.PromptFileName); fileErr == nil {\\n    if content, contentErr := file.Contents(); contentErr == nil && content != \\\"\\\" {\\n        data.Prompts = splitPromptContent(content)\\n    }\\n}\\n// Fallback: read from filesystem (written at turn start, covers mid-turn commits)\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, sessionID)\\n}\\n// Last resort: extract from transcript\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(agentType, data.Transcript, checkpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAlso revert the `turnPrompt` parameter addition from the previous attempt — it's no longer needed.\\n\\n### 3. Read `prompt.txt` from filesystem in `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` (~line 504):\\n\\nReplace transcript-based prompt extraction:\\n\\n```go\\n// Read prompts from filesystem (written at turn start)\\ndata.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, state.SessionID)\\n// Fallback: extract from transcript\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(state.AgentType, data.Transcript, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** — `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints()` (~line 2017):\\n\\nReplace transcript-based prompt extraction. At this point (turn end), the shadow branch has been updated by SaveStep, so prompt.txt is current:\\n\\n```go\\n// Read prompts from shadow branch (updated by SaveStep at turn end)\\nprompts := readPromptsFromShadowBranch(ctx, repo, state)\\n// Fallback: read from filesystem\\nif len(prompts) == 0 {\\n    prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, state.SessionID)\\n}\\n// Last resort: extract from transcript\\nif len(prompts) == 0 {\\n    prompts = extractUserPrompts(state.AgentType, string(fullTranscript))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Add helper functions\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`**:\\n\\n```go\\n// splitPromptContent splits prompt.txt content into individual prompts.\\n// Prompts are separated by \\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\" (same format as WriteCommitted).\\nfunc splitPromptContent(content string) []string {\\n    if content == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    parts := strings.Split(content, \\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n    var prompts []string\\n    for _, p := range parts {\\n        if trimmed := strings.TrimSpace(p); trimmed != \\\"\\\" {\\n            prompts = append(prompts, trimmed)\\n        }\\n    }\\n    return prompts\\n}\\n\\n// readPromptsFromFilesystem reads prompt.txt from the session metadata directory on the filesystem.\\nfunc readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) []string {\\n    sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)\\n    absDir, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(absDir, paths.PromptFileName))\\n    if err != nil || len(data) == 0 {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    return splitPromptContent(string(data))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`**:\\n\\n```go\\n// readPromptsFromShadowBranch reads prompt.txt from the session's shadow branch tree.\\nfunc readPromptsFromShadowBranch(ctx context.Context, repo *git.Repository, state *SessionState) []string {\\n    shadowBranchName := getShadowBranchNameForCommit(state.BaseCommit, state.WorktreeID)\\n    refName := plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(shadowBranchName)\\n    ref, err := repo.Reference(refName, true)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    commit, err := repo.CommitObject(ref.Hash())\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    tree, err := commit.Tree()\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    metadataDir := paths.EntireMetadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + state.SessionID\\n    file, err := tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.PromptFileName)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    content, err := file.Contents()\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    return splitPromptContent(content)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Revert previous changes\\n\\nRevert all changes from the previous attempt (FirstPrompt → LastPrompt rename, turnPrompt parameter, etc.). No session state type changes needed.\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — write prompt.txt at turn start\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — read prompt.txt from shadow branch/filesystem, add helpers, revert turnPrompt param\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — read prompt.txt from shadow branch in finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints, add helper, revert LastPrompt changes\\n\\n## Files NOT Modified (reverted from previous attempt)\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` — no FirstPrompt → LastPrompt rename\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go` — no constant rename\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go` — no field rename\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/status.go` — no field rename\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/status_test.go` — no test fixture changes\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. All existing tests pass (no changes to types/interfaces)\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":590,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":146351,\"output_tokens\":2521,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":590,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYfEADyM1SWMaxRyxPdAH\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"a3ed988a-d70a-4286-a879-f1768852a708\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T00:49:59.705Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a3ed988a-d70a-4286-a879-f1768852a708\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0d411808-78e1-4abb-b5da-ab760ebccc55\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"571-remove-contextmd-and-simplify-prompttxt-to-checkpoint-prompts-only\",\"slug\":\"serene-churning-pudding\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Write\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01JJgGfNFrA6mAATwrY1VNyY\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01JJgGfNFrA6mAATwrY1VNyY\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T00:49:59.720Z\",\"uuid\":\"017dcb5a-c65f-4cf9-921c-863041b593c8\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a3ed988a-d70a-4286-a879-f1768852a708\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0d411808-78e1-4abb-b5da-ab760ebccc55\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"571-remove-contextmd-and-simplify-prompttxt-to-checkpoint-prompts-only\",\"slug\":\"serene-churning-pudding\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01JJgGfNFrA6mAATwrY1VNyY\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"The file /Users/gtrrz-victor/.claude/plans/serene-churning-pudding.md has been updated successfully.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"aee1798f-5b17-479b-8dcd-df39800be2af\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T00:49:59.718Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"update\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/.claude/plans/serene-churning-pudding.md\",\"content\":\"# Plan: Fix prompt.txt missing in mid-turn commit checkpoints\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nMid-turn commits (agent commits while still working) produce checkpoints without `prompt.txt` after the first one. The root cause: after the first condensation advances `CheckpointTranscriptStart`, `extractCheckpointPrompts()` scopes the transcript past where the prompt lives.\\n\\nThe previous approach (repurposing `FirstPrompt` → `LastPrompt` on session state) was rejected as too invasive and not aligned with the architecture. The user wants the shadow branch to be the source of truth, not the transcript.\\n\\n## Root Cause Detail\\n\\n1. Agent commits mid-turn → PostCommit → `CondenseSession` → `extractSessionData`\\n2. First checkpoint: `extractCheckpointPrompts(transcript, offset=0)` finds the prompt ✓\\n3. After condensation: `CheckpointTranscriptStart` advances to end of transcript\\n4. If all files were committed (no carry-forward), `CheckpointTranscriptStart` stays advanced\\n5. Agent commits again → `extractCheckpointPrompts(transcript, offset=advanced)` scopes past prompt ✗\\n\\nNote: carry-forward resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0`, so this bug only manifests when all files are committed (no carry-forward).\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n**Write `prompt.txt` to the filesystem at turn start, then read it from the shadow branch or filesystem during condensation — not from the transcript.**\\n\\n### Why this works\\n- At turn start, we have the user prompt (`event.Prompt`) — write it to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt`\\n- During mid-turn condensation, read `prompt.txt` from: shadow branch tree → filesystem → transcript (fallback)\\n- At turn end, `CreateSessionCheckpoint` overwrites `prompt.txt` with the properly extracted version, then `SaveStep` commits it to the shadow branch\\n- The shadow branch remains the source of truth after SaveStep\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Write `prompt.txt` at turn start\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`** — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~line 113):\\n\\nAfter `CapturePrePromptState` and before `InitializeSession`, write the user prompt to `prompt.txt`:\\n\\n```go\\n// Write prompt.txt early so it's available for mid-turn commits.\\n// CreateSessionCheckpoint will overwrite this with the full extracted version at turn end.\\nif event.Prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)\\n    if sessionDirAbs, absErr := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir); absErr == nil {\\n        if mkErr := os.MkdirAll(sessionDirAbs, 0o750); mkErr == nil {\\n            promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)\\n            _ = os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(event.Prompt), 0o600)\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis is best-effort (errors silently ignored) — the transcript fallback still exists.\\n\\n### 2. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch in `extractSessionData`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionData()` (~line 464):\\n\\nReplace transcript-based prompt extraction with shadow branch tree read + filesystem fallback:\\n\\n```go\\n// Read prompts from shadow branch tree (source of truth after SaveStep)\\nif file, fileErr := tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.PromptFileName); fileErr == nil {\\n    if content, contentErr := file.Contents(); contentErr == nil && content != \\\"\\\" {\\n        data.Prompts = splitPromptContent(content)\\n    }\\n}\\n// Fallback: read from filesystem (written at turn start, covers mid-turn commits)\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, sessionID)\\n}\\n// Last resort: extract from transcript\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(agentType, data.Transcript, checkpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAlso revert the `turnPrompt` parameter addition from the previous attempt — it's no longer needed.\\n\\n### 3. Read `prompt.txt` from filesystem in `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` (~line 504):\\n\\nReplace transcript-based prompt extraction:\\n\\n```go\\n// Read prompts from filesystem (written at turn start)\\ndata.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, state.SessionID)\\n// Fallback: extract from transcript\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(state.AgentType, data.Transcript, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** — `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints()` (~line 2017):\\n\\nReplace transcript-based prompt extraction. At this point (turn end), the shadow branch has been updated by SaveStep, so prompt.txt is current:\\n\\n```go\\n// Read prompts from shadow branch (updated by SaveStep at turn end)\\nprompts := readPromptsFromShadowBranch(ctx, repo, state)\\n// Fallback: read from filesystem\\nif len(prompts) == 0 {\\n    prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, state.SessionID)\\n}\\n// Last resort: extract from transcript\\nif len(prompts) == 0 {\\n    prompts = extractUserPrompts(state.AgentType, string(fullTranscript))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Add helper functions\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`**:\\n\\n```go\\n// splitPromptContent splits prompt.txt content into individual prompts.\\n// Prompts are separated by \\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\" (same format as WriteCommitted).\\nfunc splitPromptContent(content string) []string {\\n    if content == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    parts := strings.Split(content, \\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n    var prompts []string\\n    for _, p := range parts {\\n        if trimmed := strings.TrimSpace(p); trimmed != \\\"\\\" {\\n            prompts = append(prompts, trimmed)\\n        }\\n    }\\n    return prompts\\n}\\n\\n// readPromptsFromFilesystem reads prompt.txt from the session metadata directory on the filesystem.\\nfunc readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) []string {\\n    sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)\\n    absDir, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(absDir, paths.PromptFileName))\\n    if err != nil || len(data) == 0 {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    return splitPromptContent(string(data))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`**:\\n\\n```go\\n// readPromptsFromShadowBranch reads prompt.txt from the session's shadow branch tree.\\nfunc readPromptsFromShadowBranch(ctx context.Context, repo *git.Repository, state *SessionState) []string {\\n    shadowBranchName := getShadowBranchNameForCommit(state.BaseCommit, state.WorktreeID)\\n    refName := plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(shadowBranchName)\\n    ref, err := repo.Reference(refName, true)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    commit, err := repo.CommitObject(ref.Hash())\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    tree, err := commit.Tree()\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    metadataDir := paths.EntireMetadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + state.SessionID\\n    file, err := tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.PromptFileName)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    content, err := file.Contents()\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil\\n    }\\n    return splitPromptContent(content)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Revert previous changes\\n\\nRevert all changes from the previous attempt (FirstPrompt → LastPrompt rename, turnPrompt parameter, etc.). No session state type changes needed.\\n\\n## Files Modified