SessionCheckpoint` in `lifecycle.go`). It's not available for mid-turn commits.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Write `prompt.txt` at turn start\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`** — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~line 131, after `CapturePrePromptState`):\\n\\nWrite the user prompt to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` so it's available for mid-turn commits. `CreateSessionCheckpoint` will overwrite it with the full extracted version at turn end.\\n\\n```go\\nif event.Prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)\\n    if sessionDirAbs, absErr := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir); absErr == nil {\\n        if mkErr := os.MkdirAll(sessionDirAbs, 0o750); mkErr == nil {\\n            _ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName), []byte(event.Prompt), 0o600)\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nBest-effort (errors silently ignored) — transcript fallback still exists as last resort.\\n\\n### 2. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch / filesystem in `extractSessionData`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionData()` (~line 464):\\n\\nReplace `extractCheckpointPrompts()` call with shadow branch tree read → filesystem fallback → transcript fallback:\\n\\n```go\\n// 1. Read from shadow branch tree (source of truth after SaveStep)\\nif file, fileErr := tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.PromptFileName); fileErr == nil {\\n    if content, contentErr := file.Contents(); contentErr == nil && content != \\\"\\\" {\\n        data.Prompts = splitPromptContent(content)\\n    }\\n}\\n// 2. Fallback: filesystem (written at turn start, covers mid-turn commits)\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, sessionID)\\n}\\n// 3. Last resort: transcript parsing\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(agentType, data.Transcript, checkpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAlso **revert** the `turnPrompt` p