id-turn commit checkpoints\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nMid-turn commits (agent commits while still working) produce checkpoints without `prompt.txt` after the first one. The root cause: `extractCheckpointPrompts()` re-parses the transcript scoped by `CheckpointTranscriptStart`, which advances past where the prompt lives after the first condensation.\\n\\nThe fix: **write `prompt.txt` to the filesystem at turn start**, then read it from the shadow branch tree or filesystem during condensation — never from the transcript.\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n1. Agent commits mid-turn → PostCommit → `CondenseSession` → `extractSessionData`\\n2. First checkpoint: `extractCheckpointPrompts(transcript, offset=0)` finds the prompt ✓\\n3. After condensation: `CheckpointTranscriptStart` advances\\n4. Agent commits again → `extractCheckpointPrompts(transcript, offset=advanced)` scopes past prompt ✗\\n\\nCurrently `prompt.txt` is only written to the filesystem at turn **end** (`CreateSessionCheckpoint` in `lifecycle.go`). It's not available for mid-turn commits.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Write `prompt.txt` at turn start\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`** — `handleLifecycleTurnStart()` (~line 131, after `CapturePrePromptState`):\\n\\nWrite the user prompt to `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` so it's available for mid-turn commits. `CreateSessionCheckpoint` will overwrite it with the full extracted version at turn end.\\n\\n```go\\nif event.Prompt != \\\"\\\" {\\n    sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)\\n    if sessionDirAbs, absErr := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir); absErr == nil {\\n        if mkErr := os.MkdirAll(sessionDirAbs, 0o750); mkErr == nil {\\n            _ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName), []byte(event.Prompt), 0o600)\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nBest-effort (errors silently ignored) — transcript fallback still exists as last resort.\\n\\n### 2. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch / filesystem in `extractSessionData`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionData()` (~line 464):\\n\\nReplace `extractCheckpointPrompts()` call with shadow branch tree read → filesystem fallback → transcript fallback:\\n\\n```go\\n// 1. Read from shadow branch tree (source of truth after SaveStep)\\nif file, fileErr := tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + paths.PromptFileName); fileErr == nil {\\n    if content, contentErr := file.Contents(); contentErr == nil && content != \\\"\\\" {\\n        data.Prompts = splitPromptContent(content)\\n    }\\n}\\n// 2. Fallback: filesystem (written at turn start, covers mid-turn commits)\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, sessionID)\\n}\\n// 3. Last resort: transcript parsing\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(agentType, data.Transcript, checkpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAlso **revert** the `turnPrompt` parameter added in the previous attempt.\\n\\n### 3. Read `prompt.txt` from filesystem in `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`** — `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` (~line 504):\\n\\nSame pattern: filesystem → transcript fallback:\\n\\n```go\\ndata.Prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, state.SessionID)\\nif len(data.Prompts) == 0 {\\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(state.AgentType, data.Transcript, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Read `prompt.txt` from shadow branch in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** — `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints()` (~line 2017):\\n\\nAt turn end, the shadow branch is updated by SaveStep so `prompt.txt` is current:\\n\\n```go\\nprompts := readPromptsFromShadowBranch(ctx, repo, state)\\nif len(prompts) == 0 {\\n    prompts = readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, state.SessionID)\\n}\\nif len(prompts) == 0 {\\n    prompts = extractUserPrompts(state.AgentType, string(fullTranscript))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Add helper functions\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`**:\\n\\n- `splitPromptContent(content string) []string` — splits prompt.txt content on `\\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\"` separator\\n- `readPromptsFromFilesystem(ctx, sessionID) []string` — reads `.entire/metadata/<session-id>/prompt.txt` from disk\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`**:\\n\\n- `readPromptsFromShadowBranch(ctx, repo, state) []string` — reads prompt.txt from shadow branch tree (reuses pattern from existing `getLastPrompt()` at line 1891)\\n\\n### 6. Revert previous attempt\\n\\nRevert all `FirstPrompt` → `LastPrompt` renames. No session state type changes needed.\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` | Write prompt.txt at turn start |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | Read prompt.txt from shadow branch/filesystem, add helpers, revert `turnPrompt` param |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Read prompt.txt from shadow branch in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints`, add helper, revert `LastPrompt` changes |\\n\\n## Files NOT Modified (revert from previous attempt)\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/status.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/status_test.go`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"f1f4c885-4524-48e3-9960-05485d4e02f5\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"61fe9fdb-4854-4984-b7c5-2cbb3b8cfb12\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0d411808-78e1-4abb-b5da-ab760ebccc55\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"571-remove-contextmd-and-simplify-prompttxt-to-checkpoint-prompts-only\",\"slug\":\"serene-churning-pudding\",\"message\":{\"mod